Description:
   Dunmar's Call is the Warden's battle cry, named after the legendary
   warrior-general Dunmar whose voice was said to fortify entire armies.
   The Warden unleashes a powerful war shout that bolsters their own fighting
   spirit and temporarily intimidates nearby opponents.

   The call grants the Warden a short-term bonus to combat stats and may
   cause weaker enemies to falter in their attacks. In group settings, the
   cry can provide a morale boost to nearby allies. The technique requires
   full physical commitment — the Warden must be in a stable standing
   position to project the full force of the call. It is an early-career
   cornerstone of the Warden's arsenal, useful both in solo combat and
   when leading a group charge.
